OL,6,FResearch suggests there can be huge
OL,7,Fbenefits for the child, mother and
OL,8,Ffather if that family unit can bond
OL,9,Funimpeded for longer periods of time
OL,10,Fafter childbirth.
OL,12,FGeorge Gabriel, co-founder of the Dad
OL,13,FShift campaign group, said: "The
OL,14,FEuropean average is dads and non-
OL,15,Fbirthing parents get eight weeks at
OL,16,F100% of earnings. We think in the UK -
OL,17,Fyou know, obviously it's a challenging
OL,18,Fmoment for the country - but six weeks
OL,19,Fat 90% of earnings would be a real
OL,20,Fstart."
