OL,6,FThat could be a problem, because the
OL,7,FUK currently has its lowest birthrate
OL,8,Fon record and an ageing population,
OL,9,Fwhich means more workers are needed to
OL,10,Fsupport a growing number of pensioners.
OL,12,FThe UK is far from alone with its low
OL,13,Fbirthrate, but other countries have
OL,14,Fenacted policies designed to encourage
OL,15,Fpeople to have more children.
OL,17,FSouth Korea, the country with the
OL,18,Fworld's lowest birth rate, has spent
OL,19,Fmore than #200 billion in the past 16
OL,20,Fyears trying to urge its citizens to
OL,21,Fhave more children.
